# App architecture (Vayeate Theme Studio)

Scope: [`vayeate-theme-studio/`](vayeate-theme-studio/).

## Layers

| Layer | Role |
|-------|------|
| `electron/` | Main process, preload, IPC — no business logic |
| `src/app/` | UI, actions, handlers, viewmodels |
| `src/domain/` | Controllers, operations, validations, state, utils |
| `src/gateway/` | Services + gateway facades over external systems |
| `src/model/` | Domain types; **zod** for validation |

## Domains (under app and domain)

`app`, `catalog`, `common`, `core`, `template`, `theme`

## Mutation flow

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  UI[Component] --> AQ[ActionQueue]
  AQ --> H[Handler]
  H --> C[Controller]
  C --> V[Validations]
  C --> O[Operations]
  O --> S[State setters]
  S --> VM[ViewModel useContextSelector]
  VM --> UI
```

- Only **UI-originated signals** on the queue — pointer/keyboard events, and React **lifecycle** moments where a screen or control **mounts or unmounts** (e.g. `*_ON_LOAD`, `*_ON_UNLOAD`, `*_ON_OPEN`). Handlers → controllers only (exhaustive switch).
- **State updates only in operations.** Controllers read via getters; never set state.
- **Exception — action queue status:** State that reflects the action queue’s own status (depth, processing flag, etc.) may be updated **only inside the `ActionQueue` implementation** (`src/app/core/actions/`), not via handler → controller → operation. **Rationale:** routing that update through a normal app action would require enqueueing an action to mutate queue state, which **cycles** through the queue. This is an intentional exception; all other domain state still updates **only** in operations.
- **Business logic only in operations.** Gateways/services: system + conversion, not domain rules.
- **Controllers** must not call other controllers; only validations and operations ([controller.mdc](controller.mdc)).

## Actions

- Shape: `<CONTROL>_<ACTION>` (e.g. `CATALOG_PAGE_ON_LOAD`).
- One action per **user or lifecycle** interaction; one type per component/event (reuse only for same control type with a discriminant field).
- **Lifecycle:** Page, panel, window, and dialog **load** and **unload** are valid action sources — enqueue the same way as click handlers (e.g. `useEffect` cleanup for unload). Treat them as **UI-originated**, not back doors around the queue.
- Payload: only user input or entity identifiers — **not** values derivable from app state.

## DI and files

- **tsyringe** **`@singleton()`** for controllers, operations, validations, gateways, services — inject **concrete types** directly; **no** string or symbol injection tokens.
- **One** top-level export per file.
- **React components** under `src/app/**` (`*.tsx` in `components/` or pages): **PascalCase** filename matching the default export (see [component.mdc](component.mdc)).
- **All other** source modules (controllers, operations, viewmodels, state, gateways, services, models, handlers, etc.): **kebab-case** filename matching export; exported **classes** **PascalCase** where applicable.

## Good / bad

| Good | Bad |
|------|-----|
| `CloseWindowController` | `HandleSaveButtonClickController` |
| Operation owns state write after validation in controller | Handler contains business rules |
| ViewModel exposes selectors | Component defines `useContextSelector` inline |
